# Central Feedback Notifications

All user-facing success/error feedback in the Quasar app goes through the shared helpers. Do **not** invent per-feature toast or error-dialog systems.

## Required API

Import from [`web/src/composables/useFeedback.ts`](web/src/composables/useFeedback.ts):

| Intent | Call | UI |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| API / hard failure | `showApiError(err, fallback?)` or `showError(message)` | Centered Dialog, **OK** only |
| Success | `showSuccess(message)` | Top toast (`Notify`) |
| Soft warning | `showWarning(message)` | Top toast |
| Info | `showInfo(message)` | Top toast |

Parse unknown API errors with [`web/src/utils/apiError.ts`](web/src/utils/apiError.ts) via `showApiError` (do not reimplement extraction).

## Banned in new / edited feature code

- `$q.notify(...)` / `Notify.create(...)` for feature feedback
- `$q.dialog(...)` / `Dialog.create(...)` for **error** messaging
- Inline `alert()`, custom toast components, or page-local error snackbars for the same purpose
- Duplicating defaults (position, timeout, OK button) in call sites

## Allowed exceptions

- **Confirm / destructive prompts** (Yes/Cancel, delete confirm) may still use Quasar `Dialog` with cancel — not for API error text.
- **Inline form field validation** (`q-input` rules / helper text) stays on the field; do not replace with the global dialog.
- Extending `useFeedback.ts` itself when adding a new global feedback kind.

## Pattern

```ts
import { showSuccess, showApiError } from 'src/composables/useFeedback';

try {
  await someRpc();
  showSuccess('Saved');
} catch (err) {
  await showApiError(err, 'Failed to save');
}
```

When touching legacy `$q.notify` negative/success calls in a file you already edit, migrate that call site to `useFeedback`.
